{
  "texts": [
    "ResNet-50 25 and VGG-16 26 facilitate the extraction of features from colorectal colonoscopy images in the PolynetDWTCADx system.",
    "Because ResNet-50's architecture is more complicated, it can pull out features from images that are more abstract and could help tell the difference between healthy and cancerous tissues.",
    "Conversely, VGG-16 endeavours to acquire more detailed features for the images.",
    "Figure 4 depicts the architecture of the RV-22 Integrated CNN.",
    "This methodology is exceedingly critical in the context of cancer detection and segmentation, as it facilitates the system's comprehension of colorectal cancer and its accurate identification and segmentation."
  ]
}